## Visual Validation with Browser MCP

After ANY UI change, validate visually using the browser MCP:

1. Confirm local server is running: `/local status`
2. Navigate to the affected page: use `browser_navigate` to `http://localhost:3000/workspace/[id]/[route]`
3. Capture state: use `browser_snapshot` to see current page structure
4. Assert key elements are present (no crashes, expected content visible)
5. Report what you saw in your response

**Page-to-validation mapping:**

| Change Type | Validate Page |
|---|---|
| Convex schema change | All major workspace tabs (agents, inbox, signals) |
| New agent definition | `/workspace/[id]/agents` — Agent Hub |
| Signal handler change | `/workspace/[id]/inbox` — Signal Inbox |
| MCP tool change | Run tool via Claude Desktop, verify output |
| MCP UI app change | `/workspace/[id]` — check InitiativeDashboardEmbed |
| New page/route | Navigate directly to the new route |
| Document/task change | `/workspace/[id]/tasks` and project detail |

---

## Required Commands Before Reporting Complete

When finishing any code change, run ALL applicable commands:

```bash
# Convex changes:
cd orchestrator && npm run test:run -- convex/__tests__/

# MCP tool changes:
cd mcp-server && npm run test:run -- src/tools/__tests__/

# UI component changes:
cd orchestrator && npm run test:e2e -- --grep "@affected-feature"

# All unit tests:
cd orchestrator && npm run test:run
```

**DO NOT report a change as complete if any test fails.**

If a test reveals a bug you introduced, fix it before reporting complete.

---

## Agent Self-Validation Checklist

Before saying "done" on any feature:

- [ ] Test file exists for every new/changed module
- [ ] All tests pass (`npm run test:run` exits 0)
- [ ] Visual validation done via browser MCP (for UI changes)
- [ ] No new TypeScript errors (`npx tsc --noEmit`)
- [ ] No new linter errors
- [ ] Test names clearly describe what they test (not "it works")

---

## Test Naming Convention

```
[module/component]: [what it does] — [expected behavior]

✅ Good: "signals.create: auto-classifies signal as feature_request when content mentions missing feature"
✅ Good: "SignalInboxPage: high-impact signal shows red badge"
❌ Bad: "test signal", "works correctly", "renders"
```

---

## What NOT to Test

- `index.ts` barrel exports
- Type definitions (`types.ts`)
- Convex `_generated/` files (auto-generated)
- Third-party library behavior (mock it instead)

---

## Quick Reference

| Layer | Test Location | Framework | Run Command |
|---|---|---|---|
| Convex functions | `convex/__tests__/` | convex-test + vitest | `npm run test:run` |
| MCP tools | `mcp-server/src/tools/__tests__/` | vitest | `npm run test:run` |
| MCP UI apps | `mcp-server/apps/[app]/__tests__/` | vitest + RTL | `npm run test:run` |
| Next.js pages | `orchestrator/e2e/tests/` | Playwright | `npm run test:e2e` |
| Visual validation | browser MCP | cursor-ide-browser | `browser_navigate` + `browser_snapshot` |
